description: Helm fashioned from a crystal looking-glass. One among the Eternal City's ritual implements. Easily broken and weak against striking attacks. Worn by those committed to high treason, it wards off the intervention of the Greater Will and its vassal Fingers.

name: Nox Monk Hood
description: Silk hood worn by the monks of the Eternal City. Long ago, the Nox invoked the ire of the Greater Will, and were banished deep underground. Now they live under a false night sky, in eternal anticipation of their liege. Of the coming age of the stars. And their Lord of Night.

name: Old Aristocrat Cowl
description: Cowl made of soft cloth. Travel attire worn by nobles in the capital. Garb favored by the aged. Abandoning their birthplace after the Shattering, these undead wanderers are the pitiful product of unending life.

name: Nox Swordstress Crown
description: Crown worn by the swordstresses of the Eternal City. These women are the personal guards of the nightmaidens, and the silk hides their eyes. Long ago, the Nox invoked the ire of the Greater Will, and were banished deep underground. Now they live under a false night sky, in eternal anticipation of their liege. Of the coming age of the stars. And their Lord of Night.

name: Okina Mask
description: A wooden mask that depicts an old man bearing his teeth. The source of the sobriquet of the great swordman of the Land of Reeds. Raises dexterity as it lowers focus.

name: Nox Swordstress Crown (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Nox Swordstress Crown.

name: Nox Monk Hood (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Nox Monk Hood.

name: Octopus Head
description: A land octopus whelp worn directly on the head. Has a lingering warmth reminiscent of human skin. Those who can withstand the smell will find its organic elasticity excellent for negating strikes.

name: Omen Helm
description: Malformed helm resembling an Omen with its horns cut off.

name: Olivinus Glintstone Crown
description: One of the glintstone crowns bestowed upon Raya Lucaria scholars whose pursuits were deemed worthy. Increases intelligence to the detriment of HP. The lineage of the Olivinus Conspectus began with the sorcerer Lusat, and its adherents continue his study of meteors.

name: Perfumer Hood
description: Hood of an Erdtree Capital perfumer.

name: Omensmirk Mask
description: Mask with long, hideously twisted horns worn by the Omenkillers. Increases strength. Bears the smirking face of an elder, twisted in wicked delight. This visage is carved in the image of the evil spirits that haunt the Omen in their nightmares.

name: Preceptor's Big Hat
description: Large hat with the movements of the stars drawn on the inside of the brim. Worn by the magic preceptors who served the Carian royals.

name: Prisoner Iron Mask
description: Iron mask forced on a prisoner convicted of an appalling crime. Thick, heavy, and utterly stifling. A foul creation designed to torment the wearer, either slowly fermenting hatred within their heart, or a spiritual fervor that is near indistinguishable from it.

name: Queen's Crescent Crown
description: A tall crown depicting the moon. Worn by Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon. Increases intelligence. When Rennala, head of both the Academy of Raya Lucaria and the Carian royal family, lost her husband Radagon, her heart went along with him. And then, those at the academy realized. That Rennala was no champion, after all.

name: Radahn Soldier Helm
description: Helm worn by soldiers who fought by General Radahn's side. Its visor is fashioned after a lion's fangs.

name: Page Hood
description: Hood worn by pages who serve the nobility and are mindful to keep them out of harm's way. The unassuming sack-like appearance befits their unseen and unknown stature.

name: Prophet Blindfold
description: Blindfold of exiled prophets who foretold misfortune — and were persecuted and driven from their homes as a result. Why hesitate, if the path leading to the future is clear? Just close your eyes, and walk.

name: Pumpkin Helm
description: An oval helmet large enough to cover any head. Very heavy and very hard. Reduces damage from headshots and impacts. The inside of the helm is pitch black, keeping the crazed warrior within from panicking. Perhaps its rather roomy interior also helps alleviate feelings of pressure and claustrophobia.

name: Radahn's Redmane Helm
description: Helm of the golden lion, with flowing red hair. Worn by General Radahn.

name: Ragged Hat (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Ragged Hat.

name: Radiant Gold Mask
description: A mask designed to resemble a blazing golden halo. Created and left behind by Lord Goldmask, a staunch pursuer of Golden Order fundamentalism. Strenthens Golden Order incantations. Its striking design represents both the brilliant inspiration that once shone upon him, and the vision of a ring that he will surely find at the end of his pursuit. "To you who seek to shine as I do, wear it well!"

name: Ragged Hat
description: Helm pieced together from scavenged metal.

name: Raya Lucarian Helm
description: Helm worn by Raya Lucaria Academy soldiers. Its brow adorned with a single cuckoo's feather.

name: Rotten Duelist Helm
description: Bronze helm decorated with innumerable snakes, eaten through by scarlet rot. Worn by gladiators who were driven from the colosseum. The wearer becomes a slightly easier target for foes.

name: Royal Remains Helm
description: Helm graced with gold human bones. Worn by the unspeaking adherent of Sir Gideon the All-Knowing.

name: Royal Knight Helm
description: Silver helm of Loretta, a Knight who served Miquella's Haligtree.

name: Redmane Knight Helm
description: Helm worn by knights who fought by General Radahn's side.

name: Sacred Crown Helm
description: Flanged iron cap adorned with a crown of unalloyed gold. Increases faith. Worn by foot soldiers sworn to the Haligtree. Who is it that Miquella shall bless, if not the low and the meek?

name: Ruler's Mask
description: Mask in the image of a wizened sage. Customary dress among lords in a smaller nation. Increases faith. Such a mask illustrates the qualities of an ideal lord: chiefly, wise and possessing a certain defanged geniality. One at the center of society often finds these qualities most expedient.

name: Scaled Helm
description: Helm worn by Old Knight Istvan. The corroded metal is reinforced with rock-hard scales, making it highly effective against non-physical attacks.

name: Shining Horned Headband
description: Headband decorated by a pair of shining horns. Worn by ancestral follower shamans.

name: Sanguine Noble Hood
description: Hood of dyed black cloth featuring gold embroidery. Worn by the nobles who serve the Lord of Blood. Known to strike from pools of blood, these assassins are missionaries come to share the gospel of accursed blood.

name: Sage Hood
description: A burgundy pointed hood. Attire of the wise sages who were deemed heretical. Evidence that the wearer was driven from town.

name: Skeletal Mask
description: Skeletal mask that tightly grips the face. Worn by the assassin's of Ravensmount.

name: Snow Witch Hat
description: Witch's pointed hat, frigid and frozen through. Of a style associated with practitioners of heretical sorcery. Strengthens cold sorcery. Once worn by the snowy crone who the young Ranni encountered deep in the woods. She was a witch, and well versed in cold sorceries. It is said that the doll that houses Ranni's soul was modeled after her. That old witch was Ranni's secret mentor.

name: Spellblade's Pointed Hat
description: Glintstone sorcerer Rogier's traveling attire, graced with an intricate, aristocratic decoration. Strengthens glintstone sorcery skills.

name: Traveling Maiden Hood
description: Hood worn by traveling maidens.

name: Silver Tear Mask
description: Mask fashioned from the corpse of a formless Silver Tear, supported by its hardened, shed husk. Greatly increases arcane to the detriment of physical attack power. To imitate the imitator is a cunning play indeed.

name: Traveler's Hat
description: Hat of a traveling perfumer of no renown.

name: Vulgar Militia Helm
description: Helm worn by lean, mean, and filthy militiamen. The upward extension serves to create an appearance of larger size, however slightly.

name: Witch's Glintstone Crown
description: One of the glintstone crowns bestowed upon Raya Lucaria scholars whose pursuits were deemed worthy.

name: Twinsage Glintstone Crown
description: One of the glintstone crowns bestowed upon Raya Lucaria scholars whose pursuits were deemed worthy. Greatly increases intelligence to the detriment of HP and stamina. Scholars of the Twinsage Conspectus were the elites of the academy, permitted to study and excel in sorceries of all kinds.

name: Veteran's Helm
description: An old helm that has seen many battles.Worn by Niall, the great veteran general of Sol.

name: White Mask
description: Bloodstained, faintly grinning mask. Worn by war surgeons who were effectively mercy killers. The Lord of Blood's curse enlivens the wearer when bloodletting occurs. Slightly raises attack power when there is blood loss nearby.

name: Tree Sentinel Helm
description: Golden helm of the heavy cavalry Tree Sentinels who serve the Erdtree.

name: Twinned Helm
description: Helm depicting entwined twins of gold and silver.

name: Vagabond Knight Helm
description: Helm of a knight banished from their motherland. Dirty and battered after enduring a lengthy vagabond journey.

name: Zamor Mask
description: Mask worn by knights of Zamor, hailed as heroes in the War against the Giants. These long-lived warriors, clad in biting, freezing winds, are said to have been the mortal enemies of the Fire Giants since time immemorial.

name: Astrologer Trousers
description: Trousers worn inside a robe. Worn by those who look to the cosmos above. They read fate in the stars, and are said to be heirs of the glintstone sorcerers. But alas, the night sky no longer cradles fate.

name: Bandit Boots
description: Leather boots worn by bandits.

name: Battlemage Legwraps
description: Legwraps worn by the scholars of the Raya Lucaria Academy, tattered from being worn on the battlefield.

name: Alberich's Trousers
description: Mad Tongue Alberich's trousers.

name: Aristocrat Boots
description: Boots made from tanned leather. Travel attire worn by nobles in the capital. Abandoning their birthplace after the shattering, these undead wanderers are the pitiful product of unending life.

name: Banished Knight Greaves
description: Thick, full set of armor covering the entire body. These greaves were worn by knights who, whether by misfortune or misdeed, were forced to abandon their homes. These fierce warriors were each and all accomplished. Perhaps that is why, despite their territorial losses, they were still named knights.

name: Blackflame Monk Greave
description: Black iron greaves featuring a flame motif.

name: Beast Champion Greaves
description: Silver greaves engraved with tiny beasts. Worn by Bernahl the Recusant.

name: Black Knife Greaves
description: Greaves used by the Black Knife Assassins. Crafted with scale armor that makes no sound. The assassins that carried out the deeds of the Night of the Black Knives were all women, and rumored to be Numen who had close ties with Marika herself.

name: Blaidd's Greaves
description: Well-worn black greaves of the man-wolf Blaidd.

name: Cleanrot Greaves
description: Greaves of the Cleanrot Knights, celebrated for their undefeated campaign in the Shattering.

name: Blue Silver Mail Skirt
description: Chainmail skirt crafted with blue silver. Worn by the wolf-riding Albinauric archers.

name: Briar Greaves
description: Battered iron greaves from a foreign land. Worn by Elemer of the Briar.

name: Brave's Legwraps
description: Greaves wrapped in thick leather. Garb worn by warriors of the frigid uplands. Has a fur lining which excels at keeping the cold at bay.

name: Commoner's Shoes
description: Modest shoes made of cloth. Standard wear for commoners of the Lands Between. Only, there are no commoners remaining with their wits about them.

name: Carian Knight Greaves
description: Greaves of the enchanted knights that once served the Carian royal family. The enchanted knights, anointed by the Lunar Queen, were all decorated heroes, were heroes of the highest honors, but fell into disarray with the decline of the royal family.

name: Cloth Trousers
description: Trousers made of coarse material, commonly worn in the Lands Between.

name: Chain Leggings
description: Leggings made of woven chain. Standard issue for ordinary soldiers. Though plain in appearance, they offer dependable protection.

name: Bloodhound Knight Greaves
description: Metal greaves of the Bloodhound Knights. The Bloodhound Knights are trained as hunters and known to be unshakable trackers. Without the use of language, each knight chooses his own master. Once the decision has been made the knight stays loyal for life.

name: Bull-goat Greaves
description: Great Horned Tragoth's greaves. Covers its wearer with a pair of giant horns, providing staunch poise.

name: Cuckoo Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by Raya Lucaria Academy knights. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Crucible Greaves
description: Greaves of the Crucible Knights who served Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. Hold the power of the crucible of life, the primordial form of the Erdtree. Strengthen Aspects of the Crucible incantations. In time, the strength shown by these knights, and even their appearance, was seen as chaotic and deserving of scorn.

name: Confessor Boots
description: Leather boots of the church confessors. The churches outside the Lands Between, dedicated to the teachings of the Two Fingers, send confessors out to follow the guidance of grace. The confessors are loyal servants to the Two Fingers, ready to hunt down and quietly dispose of their enemies.

name: Drake Knight Greaves
description: Greaves wrapped in thick leather. Garb worn by warriors of the frigid uplands. Has a fur lining which excels at keeping the cold at bay.

name: Consort's Trousers
description: Fine white trousers, perfectly suited for wearing beneath a silk robe.

name: Deathbed Smalls
description: Skirt worn by Phia, the Deathbed Companion.

name: Eccentric's Breeches
description: The knight Jerren's breeches. Jerren preferred a nomadic existence, but after spending time as a guest of the Carian royals, he became the guest commander for General Radahn. And for the first time, the restless tumbleweed would be bound by honorable oath.

name: Duelist Greaves
description: Greaves encircles by bronze snakes. Worn by gladiators who were driven from the colosseum. The wearer becomes a slightly easier target for foes. The snake is viewed as a traitor to the Erdtree, and the audience delighted in seeing these bronze effigies beaten and battered.

name: Elden Lord Greaves
description: Greaves of Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. The age of the Erdtree began amongst conflict, when Godfrey was lord of the battlefield. He led the War against the Giants. Faced the Storm Lord, alone. And then, there came a moment. When his last worthy enemy fell. And it was then, as the story is told, that the hue of Lord Godfrey's eyes faded.

name: Depraved Perfumer Trousers
description: Trousers worn by depraved perfumers.

name: Errant Sorcerer Boots
description: Commonplace leather boots, sturdy enough to withstand a long journey.

name: Fire Prelate Greaves
description: Black iron greaves with the appearance of flames. Attire of the Fire Prelates, commanders of the Fire Monks.

name: Fur Leggings
description: Leggings fashioned from bristly pelts. Worn by ancestral follower warriors. The ancestral followers keep their distance from the Erdtree, awaiting new buds. They are certain to sprout from their very flesh, and indeed, their souls.

name: Fingerprint Greaves
description: Iron greaves singed and blistered by fingers. Worn by Vyke, knight of the Roundtable Hold. No other Tarnished was closer to the throne of the Elden Lord than Vyke. But without announcement, Vyke traveled far below the capital, and was scorched by the flame of frenzy. Did he make his choice for his maiden, or did some other force lure him with suggestion?

name: Finger Maiden Shoes
description: Shoes worn by maidens who serve the Two Fingers. The maidens live to serve a chosen Tarnished, sharing their guidance and the wisdom of the Two Fingers. The guidance of grace would ensure that the pair be brought together. Or at least, such was the promise long ago.

name: Exile Greaves
description: Damaged iron greaves. Worn by soldiers sent to the penal colonies.

name: Foot Soldier Greaves
description: Metal Graves that have already been mended countless times. Widely issued to foot soldiers in a lord's army.

name: Gelmir Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by knights once loyal to Praetor Rykard. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Godrick Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by knights loyal to Godrick the Grafted. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Fire Monk Greaves
description: Black iron greaves featuring a flame motif. Attire of the Fire Monks.

name: Godrick Soldier Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers loyal to Godrick the Grafted. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Gold Waistwrap
description: Waistwrap made in the image of Erdtree branches. A minimal adornment made by Lord Goldmask's disciples. Those disciples have long since left him.

name: Haligtree Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by knights sworn to the Haligtree. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Godskin Apostle Trousers
description: Trousers made by seweing together patches of smooth skin.

name: Hoslow's Greaves
description: Garish silver greaves decorated with red embellishments. Passed down through the Hoslow family.

name: Haligtree Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers sworn to the Haligtree. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Godskin Noble Trousers
description: Trousers made by sewing together patches of smooth skin. Subcutaneous fat makes them plump and soft. Worn by Godskin Nobles. Nobles are the most ancient apostles who are said to have assimilated inhuman physiology. Not unlike the crucible, the Erdtree in its primordial form.

name: Guardian Greaves
description: Engraved golden greaves. Worn by the guardians of the Minor Erdtrees.

name: Kaiden Trousers
description: Trousers worn by Kaiden sellswords.

name: Knight Greaves
description: Iron greaves of an unknown knight. It is made of thin iron plate. Such metal armor is heavy, but provides considerable damage negation.

name: Land Of Reeds Greaves
description: Greaves wrapped in tough leather.

name: Leather Boots
description: Lightweight and battle-proven leather boots worn by a savvy soldier. Many admire the wearer of this armor for his chivalrous and forthright spirit.

name: Leather Trousers
description: Well-made leather trousers. The lower legs are each bound in cord for ease of movement.

name: Leyndell Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by knights sworn to defend the royal capital of Leyndell. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Leyndell Soldier Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers sworn to defend the royal capital of Leyndell. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Lionel's Greaves
description: Rounded iron greaves. Worn by Lionel the Lionhearted.

name: Malformed Dragon Greaves
description: Malformed golden greaves.

name: Malenia's Greaves
description: Greaves made of unalloyed gold. Worn by Malenia, Blade of Miquella. Malenia awaited Miquella at the foot of the husk. "My brother will keep his promise. He possesses the wisdom, the allure, of a god—he is the most fearsome Empyrean of all."

name: Maliketh's Greaves
description: Beast's greaves made of black iron and decorated with gold. Worn by Maliketh the Black Blade. Maliketh, Queen Marika's loyal half-brother, bore a blade imbued with Destined Death, and there was not one demigod who did not fear him. Champions knew what was at stake. Indeed, that is what made them champions.

name: Mausoleum Greaves
description: Greaves worn by headless soldiers who endlessly guard the Wandering Museum. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Mausoleum Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by headless knights who endlessly guard the Wandering Mausoleum. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Old Sorcerer Legwraps
description: Ragged waistcloth that extends to the thighs. Common amongst old-fashioned sorcerers.

name: Nox Monk Greaves
description: Greaves worn by the monks of the Eternal City. Long ago, the Nox invoked the ire of the Greater Will, and were banished deep underground. Now they live under a false night sky, in eternal anticipation of their liege. Of the coming age of the stars. And their Lord of Night.

name: Omenkiller Boots
description: Long, stiff leather gloves worn by the Omenkillers.

name: Nomadic Merchant's Trousers
description: Trousers of the nomadic merchants. These merchants once thrived as the Great Caravan, but after being accused of heretical beliefs, their entire clan was rounded up and buried alive far underground. Then, they chanted a curse of despair, and summoned the flame of frenzy.

name: Page Trousers
description: Trousers worn by pages who serve nobility and are mindful to keep them out of harm's way.

name: Night's Cavalry Greaves
description: Pitch-black greaves thinly painted with dried blood. Worn by the Night's Cavalry who ride funeral steeds.

name: Mushroom Legs
description: Mushrooms found growing all over the body. These overgrown mushroom have colonized the Legs.  To those enraptured by the scarlet rot, they are holy vestments that root one to the earth.

name: Omen Greaves
description: Malformed greaves resembling an Omen with its horns cut off.

name: Old Aristocrat Shoes
description: Hard-wearing shoes made of leather. Travel attire worn by nobles in the capital. Garb favored by the aged.

name: Noble's Trousers
description: White trousers of superior craftsmanship. Worn by expatriated royalty. A gift of such rare beauty, a royal wouldn't disgrace their illustrious heritage even if found dead, in a ditch, in the middle of nowhere, while wearing such splendid raiment.

name: Ragged Loincloth
description: Greaves pieced together from scavenged metal.

name: Perfumer Sarong
description: Sarong of an Erdtree Capital perfumer.

name: Preceptor's Trousers
description: Trousers of the magic preceptors who serve the Carian royals. Black and perfectly discreet.

name: Prophet Trousers
description: Trousers of the exiled prophets who foresaw that their faith would end in flames — and were persecuted and driven from their homes as a result. Its fabric scrapes against their skin like a file, and the rickety cart wheel around the neck warns passers-by not to lend an ear to their meandering sermons.

name: Queen's Leggings
description: Leggings indicating the highest order of sorcerer. Worn by Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon. When Rennala, head of both the Academy of Raya Lucaria and the Carian royal family, lost her husband Radagon, her heart went along with him. And then, those at the academy realized. That Rennala was no champion, after all.

name: Raya Lucarian Greaves
description: Greaves worn by Raya Lucaria Academy soldiers. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Prisoner Trousers
description: Tattered trousers. Worn by a prisoner convicted of an appalling crime. Never once washed, every fiber is filthy. The smell is beyond belief.

name: Redmane Knight Greaves
description: Black iron greaves worn by knights who fought by General Radahn's side. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Radahn's Greaves
description: Greaves depicting the golden lion. Worn by General Radahn.

name: Radahn Soldier Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers who fought by General Radahn's side. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Royal Knight Greaves
description: Silver greaves of Loretta, a knight who served Miquella's Haligtree. Loretta, once a royal Carian knight, went on a journey in search of a haven for Albinaurics, and determined that the Haligtree was their best chance for eventual salvation.

name: Ronin's Greaves
description: Greaves of the man who calls himself Shabriri. Highly functional and heavily worn.

name: Royal Remains Greaves
description: Greaves graced with gold human bones. Worn by the unspeaking adherent of Sir Gideon the All-Knowing.

name: Sage Trousers
description: Thick burgundy trousers. Attire of the wise sages who were deemed heretical. Evidence that the wearer was driven from town.

name: Shaman Leggings
description: Leggings fashioned from bristly pelts. Worn by ancestral follower shamans.

name: Snow Witch Skirt
description: Witch's skirt in the color of snow. Once worn by the snowy crone who the young Ranni encountered deep in the woods. She was a witch, and well versed in cold sorceries. It is said that the doll that houses Ranni's soul was modeled after her. That old witch was Ranni's secret mentor.

name: Scaled Greaves
description: Gauntlets worn by Old Knight Istvan. The corroded metal is reinforced with rock-hard scales, making it high effective against non-physical attacks. Istvan is one of a few wizened Tarnished who survived to this day.

name: Rotten Duelist Greaves
description: Greaves wrapped with bronze snakes, eaten through by scarlet rot. Worn by gladiators who were driven from the colosseum. The wearer becomes a slightly easier target for foes.

name: Spellblade's Trousers
description: Glintstone sorcerer Rogier's traveling attire, graced with an intricate, aristocratic decoration. Strengthens glintstone sorcery skills.

name: Sorcerer Leggings
description: Leggings worn by Raya Lucaria's magic scholars. Made by wrapping a simple cloth around the legs.

name: Traveler's Slops
description: Slops of a traveling perfumer of no renown.

name: Veteran's Greaves
description: An old greaves that has seen many battles.Worn by Niall, the great veteran general of Sol.

name: Traveler's Boots
description: Light yet sturdy leather boots.

name: Traveling Maiden Boots
description: Boots worn by traveling maidens.

name: Twinned Greaves
description: Greaves depicting entwined twins of gold and silver.

name: Tree Sentinel Greaves
description: Golden greaves of the heavy cavalry Tree Sentinels who serve the Erdtree.

name: War Surgeon Trousers
description: Bloodstained trousers of the war surgeons who were effectively mercy killers. Of the surgeons that were abducted by the Lord of Blood none were able to tame the accursed blood. None but Varré, that is; though he was an exception

name: Vulgar Militia Greaves
description: Greaves worn by lean, mean, and filthy militiamen.

name: Warrior Greaves
description: Greaves of a nomadic warrior. Crafted from sturdy leather.

name: Vagabond Knight Greaves
description: Greaves of a knight banished from their motherland. Dirty and battered after enduring a lengthy vagabond journey.

name: White Reed Greaves
description: Greaves of the White Reeds, fashioned from banded iron plates. Worn by the Inabam head disciples of the great swordsman Okina. The Inaba traveled in pursuit of not only the master who abandoned them, but also proper deaths, won honorably through hard-fought combat. To be a White Reed is to seek death; fitting for the Inaba, who desired nothingmore than to die by the sword.

name: Zamor Legwraps
description: Legwraps worn by knights of Zamor, hailed as heroes in the War against the Giants. These long-lived warriors, clad in biting, freezing winds, are said to have been the mortal enemies of the Fire Giants since time immemorial.

name: Buckler
description: A small metal roundshield. The bump in the center enables parrying techniques. A well-timed parry can break an enemy's stance, allowing a critical hit. Best suited for those prepared to take the risk to reap their reward.

name: Perfumer's Shield
description: Golden shield used by the perfumers of Leyndell during military service. Made to be thin and light of weight, even those lacking strength can employ this immunity-boosting shield.

name: Man-serpent's Shield
description: Small copper dome-shaped roundshield carried by the man-serpents of Mt. Gelmir. Said to have been tempered in lava, it boasts great resistance to fire.

name: Pillory Shield
description: Pillory made to punish serious felons, used as a shield. Though made of good, sturdy wood, it is only a makeshift tool and performs as such. Perhaps due to its use as a device with which the guilty were made to endure prolonged suffering, it raises vitality.

name: Rickety Shield
description: A creaky old wooden shield, circular in shape. Roughly reinforced with vines or some such. There are countless other shields available of better make. This piece of scrap isn't worth the effort of equipping.

name: Beastman's Jar-shield
description: Shield fashioned from a tall broken jar carried by the beastmen of Farum Azula. There is a particular knack to wielding it. The beastmen have always fired earthenware jars for the express purpose of making shields. Such are their ways, strange though they are.

name: Red Thorn Roundshield
description: A small, wooden roundshield. It is light and easy to use, but cannot offer the damage negation of a metal shield. Its emblem is an ancient red thorn design. Though it isn't much, it boosts fire damage negation.

name: Riveted Wooden Shield
description: Small wooden roundshield that has been reinforced with metal. It is light and easy to handle, but cannot offer the damage negation of a true metal shield. The design riveted to the center represents both sword and tree.

name: Scripture Wooden Shield
description: A small, wooden roundshield. It is light and easy to handle, but cannot offer the damage negation of a metal shield. An ancient cipher engraving linesd the circumference. Though it isn't much, it boosts holy damage negation.

name: Blue-white Wooden Shield
description: Small wooden roundshield that has been reinforced with metal. It is light and easy to handle, but cannot offer the damage negation of a true metal shield. The design is said to represent the stars of the night sky, portending fate.

name: Rift Shield
description: Small metal roundshiled depicting a sinister rift. An antiquated charm that glares back at an enemy, it boosts focus.

name: Iron Roundshield
description: An ordinary small roundshield made of metal. Heavier than a wooden shield, but boasts higher damage negation. Finely balanced, this shield is easy to use.

name: Smoldering Shield
description: Small shield made upon Mt. Gelmir forged from uncooling lava. Resists frost with its heat, and can even be used to deal fire damage if wielded as a weapon.

name: Gilded Iron Shield
description: Small metal roundshield. Heavier than a wooden shield, but boasts higher damage negation. Though the gold leaf is peeling and the effect is slight, it still boosts holy damage negation.

name: Ice Crest Shield
description: Small metal roundshield. Heavier than a wooden shield, but boasts higher damage negation. The ice crest originates from a Carian princess. Thogh the effect is slight, it boosts magic damage negation and resistance to frost.

name: Spiralhorn Shield
description: Small shield of antlers arranged in an eddy-like pattern. If used to attack a foe, the shield's antlers inflict blood loss. Once given to a Tarnished warrior who cultivated close ties to the ancestral followers. Though the effect is only slight, it boosts immunity, robustness, and focus.

name: Marred Leather Shield
description: Leather shield of Stormveil soldiers. Miuch like the castle, it is marred by mottling and thorns. Some say it is the curse of grafting which causes such affliction, while others talk of its root being something altogether more sinister hidden deep within the castle.

name: Marred Wooden Shield
description: "Wooden shield of the Stormveil soldiers. Much like the castle, it is marred by mottling and thorns. Some say it is the curse of grafting which causes such affliction, while others talk of its root being something altogether more sinister hidden deep within the castle."

name: Coil Shield
description: An extremely odd shield adorned with a coiled bronze snake. An excellent choice for attention-seekers. This Shield provides an effective defense against poison - after all, how does one poison a poisonous snake?

name: Kite Shield
description: A standard medium-sized metal shield. Metal shields reliably negate physical damage when guarding, a trait which made them highly trusted on the battlefield.

name: Banished Knight's Shield
description: A tall medium-sized metal shield. Given to knights who, whether by misfortune or misdeed, were forced to abandon their homes. Most of these knights were sent to the fringes, where they were forced to start anew with only despair for company.

name: Albinauric Shield
description: Tall oval shield made of metal carried by young Albinaurics. The ornamentation represents the primordial drop of dew from which they are said to have been created. Boasts exceptional magic damage negation. The Albinaurics' most formidable foes were sorcerers, after all.

name: Sun Realm Shield
description: Shield of honor depicting a city crowned by the sun. It has seen better days. Much like the wear upon the shield, the Seat of the Sun is long faded away.

name: Silver Mirrorshield
description: Shield of radiant silver, festooned with amber and carried by Loretta, Knight of the Haligtree. The shape is said to imitate that of a sacred drop of dew, which inspired the absurd rumor that Loretta herself was an Albinauric.

name: Round Shield
description: A wooden roundshield that has been reinforced with metal. Comparatively light for its size, this shield is easy to handle but lacks a true metal shield's ability to negate damage.

name: Scorpion Kite Shield
description: A standard medium-sized metal shield. Highly reputed for its solid build and reliability. Emblazoned with a yellow scorpion, a warning of surprise attacks and sudden strikes.

name: Twinbird Kite Shield
description: Shield featuring a vividly painted twinbird. The twinbird is said to be the envoy of an outer god, and mother of the Deathbirds. At dwindling levels of HP, this shield slightly boosts both attack and defense.

name: Blue-gold Kite Shield
description: A standard medium-sized shield. Highly reputed for its solid build and reliability. The design represents the Erdtree foreground against a blue sky.

name: Brass Shield
description: On the larger side for medium-sized shield, the face has been covered in brass. Commonly employed in the Shattering.

name: Shield Of The Guilty
description: Shield made to venerate a maiden whose eyes were crushed by Briars of Sin before being reborn in these lands. Venerating the repose of the soul, this shield boosts focus. The briars can be used to attack foes.

name: Great Turtle Shell
description: Shield fashioned from a great turtle shell. The natural curve helps it contend with foes' attacks. The turtle is a symbol of tirelessness, and this shield boosts stamina recovery speed.

name: Carian Knight's Shield
description: A teardrop-shaped shield embedded with blue glintstones. Carried by knights who served the Carian royal family. Excels when facing magic or holy attacks. Just who were these knights preparing to fight?

name: Horse Crest Wooden Shield
description: A tall, medium-sized wooden shield. Light for its size, and easy to handle. The circular horsehead design evokes a swift gallop.

name: Candletree Wooden Shield
description: A tall, medium-sized wooden shield. Light for its size, and easy to handle. Thought to represent a surreptitious prophecy of cardinal sin, the lit candle-tree design was forbidden.

name: Large Leather Shield
description: A round shield covered in leather. One of the larger categories of medium-sized shield. Though its damage negation may be lacking compared to a metal shield, it can handle wider range of attack affinities.

name: Flame Crest Wooden Shield
description: A tall, medium-sized wooden shield. Light for its size, and easy to handle. Carried by soldiers of the village that is afflicted by frenzy. The yellow flame is the symbol of the affliction, serving as a warning to those who might approach the village.

name: Hawk Crest Wooden Shield
description: A tall, medium-sized wooden shield. Light for its size, and easy to handle. Adorned with a long-forgotten crest of Stormveil, ancient in design.

name: Beast Crest Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield. Easier to handle than a kite shield. Features a beast as its crest, serving to remind warriors not to succumb to the arousal of battle. Fight with passion, but become nor its prisoner.

name: Red Crest Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield. Easier to handle than a kite shield. The crest symbolizes red wings.

name: Eclipse Crest Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield. Easier to handle than a kite shield. The sun in eclipse is said to be the symbol of the Wandering Mausoleum where the soulless demigods slumber.

name: Blue Crest Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield. Easier to handle than a kite shield. The crest represents a forest and river.

name: Inverted Hawk Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield. Easier to handle than a kite shield. The inverted hawk is the emblem of the company of slaves ordered to explore the Eternal City.

name: Heater Shield
description: A medium-sized metal shield, comparatively easy to handle. Metal shields reliably negate physical damage when guarding, a trait which made them highly trusted on the battlefield.

name: Black Leather Shield
description: Roundshield covered in black leather. On the larger side for a medium-sized shield. From the north, this shield depicts the polar star in rivets of gold. The inside is lined with fur, protecting the carrier from frost.

name: Dragon Towershield
description: Tower shield engraved with a dragon, symbol of protection. Heavy even among greatshields, it possesses exceptional guarding ability The ancient dragons, who ruled in the prehistoric era before the Erdtree, would protect their lord as a wall of living rock.

name: Crucible Hornshield
description: Greatshield of red-tinged gold carried by Crucible Knights. Features a great horn. An ancient holiness dwells within. The crucible horn skewers foes when performing shield bashes.

name: Distinguished Greatshield
description: Greatshield featuring sumptuous ornamentation used by the scions of great families. Due to their excessive size, these shields were at times seen as the hallmark of little lordlings who were too timid to earn a few nicks and scratches.

name: Dragonclaw Shield
description: Greatshield said to have been whittled from the claw of a great, ancient dragon, wielded by grotesque Tree Sentinels who yet serve the Edrtree. Imbued with lightning.

name: Golden Beast Crest Shield
description: Shield of dull gold with a beast engraved as its crest. Lighter than most greratshields, and subsequently easier to wield. The beast depicted is Serosh, aged counselor who guides the golden lineage.

name: Erdtree Greatshield
description: Weighty greatshield forged of gold carried by the order of Tree Sentinels, heavily equipped knights. Blessed by an old incantation of protection. The living rampart of the Erdtree, the Tree Sentinels are the standard to which all defenders of the Erdtree aspire.

name: Briar Greatshield
description: Greatshield from a foreign land, used by Elemer of the Briar. Attacks with this armament utilize the iron thorns that have been wound around its frame. Originates from Eochaid, a land of proudly solitary ascetics.

name: Jellyfish Shield
description: The head of a spirit jellyfish, commonly found floating above sacred ground throughout the Lands Between, wielded without modification as a shield. The see-through head is extremely light, but its flesh is supple, providing absolutely no protection from piercing attacks

name: Fingerprint Stone Shield
description: A great stone shield with an intricately carved fingerprint design. One of the heaviest of all greatshields. Part of the tomb of an ancient god, the Readerless Fingers relayed their message through these imprints, said to be the very seeds from which frenzy first sprouted.

name: Icon Shield
description: Greatshield painted with a divine scene; the recipients of a blessed tear from the Erdtree. An item that looks back fondly on the age of plenty. The divine scene acts in and of itself as a sacred invocation; gradually restoring the carrier's HP.

name: Visage Shield
description: Tricksome bronze shield depicting the face of a Fire Giant. Several tongues leap from its open mouth. The dreadful visage and burning flames are designed to remind one of the horror of facing a Fire Giant. In other words, this shield has an instructional function.

name: One-eyed Shield
description: Tricksome shield made from white stone depicting a malformed one-eyed god. The barrel of a firearm pokes through the open mouth. Once worshipped by the giants, this evil deity is believed to have been slain by Queen Marika.

name: Spiked Palisade Shield
description: Designed to perform shield bashes, these attacks riddle the enemy with holes, earning it the nickname of "pard shield"

name: Manor Towershield
description: An iron greatshield large enough to cover the entire body. Depicts the Roundtable Hold, gathering place of champions. Greatshields boast high damage negation and guard capacity, making enemy attacks easy to repel.

name: Crossed-tree Towershield
description: An iron greatshield large enough to cover the entire body. Emblazoned with an old, interleaving tree. Greatshields boast high damage negation and guard capacity, making enemy attacks easy to repel

name: Redmane Greatshield
description: Greatshield shaped like a fang, featuring the crest of red-maned lion. Carried by the Redmane Knights who fought alongside Radahn.

name: Ant's Skull Plate
description: Huge head of one of the giant ants which inhabit the two underground rivers, used without modification as a shield. Excels at repeling enemy attacks. Giant ants are venomous creatures, granting a boost to immunity when wielding the shield.

name: Inverted Hawk Towershield
description: An iron greatshield large enough to cover the entire body. Features an inverted hawk crest. Greatshields boast high damage negation and guard capacity, making enemy attacks easy to repel.

name: Eclipse Crest Greatshield
description: Metal greatshield painted with a sun in eclipse. Carried by the headless mausoleum knights. The eclipsed sun, drained of color, is the protective star of soulless demigods. It aids the mausoleum knights by keeping Destined Death at bay. No skill. This armament has no skill. If the armament in the other hand has a skill, that skill will be used instead.

name: Cuckoo Greatshield
description: Metal Greatshield painted with a peering cuckoo. Carried by the enchanted knights sworn to the academy. Boasting high magic damage negation, this shield is used to hunt down mages. Our Enemys is none other then caria itself

name: Gilded Greatshield
description: Metal greatshield coated with gold. Carried by knights loyal to Godrick. The red tinge in the gold coat mirrors the primordial matter that became the Erdtree. The color of homeward yearning.

name: Golden Greatshield
description: Oval greatshield made of gold, carried by knights who protect the Royal Capital of Leyndell. Knights of Leyndell are reputed for their sturdiness, exemplified by this shield's exceptional guard capacity.

name: Haligtree Crest Greatshield
description: Metal greatshield depicting the Haligtree with unalloyed gold. Carried by knights who have vowed to serve Miquella's Haligtree. Possesses high holy damage negation. Yet now, with the Haligtree misshapen, this wondrous rendition is a fleeting fantasy.

name: Wooden Greatshield
description: Wooden greatshield reinforced with a metal ornamentation. Greatshields boast high damage negation and guard capacity, making enemy attacks easy to repel.

name: Lordsworn's Shield
description: Wooden tower shield. Lightweightfor a greatshield and easy to handle. Commonly used in the Shattering. Greatshields boast high damage negation and guard capacity, making enemy attacks easy to repel.

name: Arrow's Sting Talisman
description: A talisman depicting three iron arrows. Carried by soldiers long ago.

name: Arsenal Charm
description: An iron charm that resembles a mass of weaponry. Boosts maximum equipment load. This talisman was derived from an unusual greatsword, once wielded by a hero hungry for vengeance.

name: Assassin's Cerulean Dagger
description: An assassin's dagger, misshapen and stained in cerulean. Critical hits restore FP.

name: Assassin's Crimson Dagger
description: An assassin's dagger, misshapen and stained in crimson. Critical hits restore HP.

name: Arrow's Reach Talisman
description: A talisman depicting three arrows. Carried by hunters of beasts.

name: Axe Talisman
description: A talisman depicting an axe and a warrior. Enhances charge attacks.

name: Boltdrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a yellow ancient dragon. Boosts lightning damage negation.

name: Blue Dancer Charm
description: A cloth doll depicting a dancer garbed in blue. An ancient heirloom of some sort.

name: Blessed Dew Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a drop of the Erdtree's sap, a blessed boon.

name: Bull-goat's Talisman
description: A talisman depicting the horns of a bull-goat. Raises poise.

name: Cerulean Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with cerulean amber inlaid. Boosts maximum FP.

name: Carian Filigreed Crest
description: A talisman adorned with the royal crest.

name: Cerulean Seed Talisman
description: A cerulean-colored talisman patterned after an Erdtree seed. Boosts FP restoration from the Flask of Cerulean Tears.

name: Clarifying Horn Charm
description: An accoutrement worn by the ancestral followers. Raises focus. (Focus governs resistance to sleep and madness.)

name: Claw Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a claw and an assassin. Enhances jump attacks.

name: Crucible Knot Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from a bony knot that embodies that aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago.

name: Crimson Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with Crimson amber inlaid. Boosts maximum HP. The Erdtree's old sap becomes amber, treasured as the most precious of jewels in the age of Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. A primordial life energy resides inside

name: Crucible Scale Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from a scale that embodies the aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago.

name: Crepus's Vial
description: Small mysterious bottle with a dark mist sealed within.

name: Curved Sword Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a curved sword and a swordsman. Enhances guard counters.

name: Dragoncrest Shield Talisman
description: Wrought iron talisman depicting a trio of ancient dragons. Boosts physical damage negation.

name: Flamedrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a red ancient dragon. Boosts fire damage negation.

name: Fire Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that burns with fire.

name: Godskin Swaddling Cloth
description: Sacred cloth of the Godskin Apostles, made from supple skin sewn together.

name: Faithful's Canvas Talisman
description: A talisman bearing an icon that depicts a group of masked figures. Raises potency of incantations.

name: Great-jar's Arsenal
description: A charm that resembles a great jar overflowing with weaponry. Vastly boosts maximum equipment load.

name: Haligdrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a golden ancient dragon. Boosts holy damage negation.

name: Green Turtle Talisman
description: A talisman in the shape of a green turtle. Raises stamina recovery speed.

name: Hammer Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a hammer and a knight. Enhances stamina-reducing attacks against a blocking opponent.

name: Immunizing Horn Charm
description: An accountrement worn by the ancestral followers. Raises immunity. (Immunity governs resistance to poison and rot.)

name: Kindred Of Rot's Exultation
description: A talisman depicting the exultation of pests.

name: Lightning Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that sparks with lightning.

name: Longtail Cat Talisman
description: A brooch depicting Lacrima, the long-tailed cat.

name: Marika's Scarseal
description: An eye engraved with an Elden Rune. Said to be the seal of Queen Marika.

name: Lord Of Blood's Exultation
description: A talisman depicting the exultation of the Lord of Blood.

name: Mottled Necklace
description: A vividly-colored accoutrement precious to the ancestral followers.

name: Moon Of Nokstella
description: This legendary talisman is a treasure of Nokstella, the Eternal City.

name: Old Lord's Talisman
description: A legendary talisman depicting the ancient king whose seat lies at the heart of the storm beyond time.

name: Pearldrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a pearlescent ancient dragon. Boosts non-physical damage negation.

name: Primal Glintstone Blade
description: An old glintstone blade that has been stained with blood.

name: Prince Of Death's Pustule
description: A fetid pustule taken from facial flesh. Raises vitality. (Vitality governs resistance to the effects of Death.)

name: Radagon Icon
description: A legendary talisman depicting the Elden Lord Radagon. Shortens the casting time of sorceries and incantations.

name: Radagon's Scarseal
description: An eye engraved with an Elden Rune. Said to be the seal of King Consort Radagon.

name: Radagon's Soreseal
description: This legendary talisman is an eye engraved with an Elden Rune, said to be the seal of King Consort Radagon.

name: Sacred Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart with a blessed glow.

name: Sacrificial Twig
description: A talisman fashioned from a dried twig, so slender that it might snap at the slightest touch.

name: Shabriri's Woe
description: Disturbing likeness of a man whose eyes have been gouged out. The corners of his mouth are upturned in an almost flirtatious manner.

name: Spelldrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a blue ancient dragon. Boosts magic damage negation.

name: Stargazer Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with the legend of a queen. Raises intelligence.

name: Twinblade Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a twinblade and a confessor. Enhances the final hit ending a chain of attacks.

name: Taker's Cameo
description: A talisman engraved with a stern likeness of Praetor Rykard, master of Volcano Manor.

name: Starscourge Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with a scene from a heroic tale. Raises strength.

name: Viridian Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with viridian amber inlaid. Boosts maximum stamina. The Erdtree's old sap becomes amber, treasured as the most precious of jewels in the age of Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. A primordial life energy resides inside

name: Two Fingers Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with the legend of the Two Fingers. Raises faith.

name: Winged Sword Insignia
description: A talisman depicting a raised prosthetic blade. An honor bestowed upon the knights who fought alongside Malenia the Severed.

name: Erdtree's Favor
description: A talisman depicting a special blessing of the Erdtree. Slightly raises maximum HP, stamina, and equip load.

name: Crimson Seed Talisman
description: A crimson-colored talisman patterned after an Erdtree seed. Boosts HP restoration from the Flask of Crimson Tears.

name: Graven-school Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a school of graven mages, the nightmare of the academy.

name: Godfrey Icon
description: A legendary talisman depicting the Elden Lord Godfrey. Raises charge attack power of sorceries, incantations, and skills.

name: Lance Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a lance and a knight. Enhances attacks while on horseback.

name: Graven-mass Talisman
description: A talisman depicting the first school of graven mages — a nightmare that would continue to haunt the academy.  Greatly raises potency of sorceries.  The primeval current is a forbidden tradition of glintstone sorcery. To those who cleave to its teachings, the act of collecting sorcerers to fashion them into the seeds of stars is but another path of scientific inquiry.

name: Ancestral Spirit's Horn
description: Item cut from the horns of the Regal Ancestor Spirit.

name: Stalwart Horn Charm
description: An accoutrement worn by the ancestral followers. Greatly raises robustness. (Robustness governs resistance to blood loss and frost.)  Said to be a budding horn. The ancestral followers believe that the horns of a long-lived beast continue to bud like antlers, over and over again, until the beast one day becomes an ancestral spirit.

name: Dragoncrest Greatshield Talisman
description: Legendary talisman of wrought iron depicting a massive ancient dragon. Enormously boosts physical damage negation.

name: Marika's Soreseal
description: This legendary talisman is an eye engraved with an Elden Rune, said to be the seal of Queen Marika.

name: Gold Scarab
description: A talisman facsimile of a scarab, the carrier of treasures and precious things.

name: Ritual Sword Talisman
description: A talisman patterned after swords used in ritual combat held to honor the Erdtree.

name: Ritual Shield Talisman
description: A talisman patterned after shields used in ritual combat held to honor the Erdtree.

name: Perfumer's Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a set of perfume bottles. Raises potency of perfume items.

name: Blue-feathered Branchsword
description: A talisman adorned with blue feathers, once used in ancient death rituals.

name: Magic Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that shimmers with magic.

name: Prince Of Death's Cyst
description: A fetid, overgrown cyst taken from facial flesh. Greatly raises vitality. (Vitality governs resistance to the effects of Death.)

name: Warrior Jar Shard
description: Shard of a shattered warrior jar.

name: Shard Of Alexander
description: Shard of the late Alexander, a shattered warrior jar.

name: Greatshield Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a knight holding a greatshield. Boosts guarding ability.

name: Millicent's Prosthesis
description: Part of the golden prosthesis used by Millicent. The hand is locked into a fist that once raised a sword aloft.

name: Spear Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a spear and a soldier. Enhances the counterattacks that are unique to thrusting weapons.

name: Dagger Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a dagger and a surgeon. Enhances critical hits.

name: Red-feathered Branchsword
description: A talisman adorned with red feathers, once used in ancient death rituals.

name: Companion Jar
description: A talisman given by the jars to their friends. Raises potency of thrown jars.

name: Flock's Canvas Talisman
description: A talisman bearing an icon that depicts a mass of masked figures. Greatly raises potency of incantations.

name: Concealing Veil
description: Talisman put together from dark cloth with a lustrous sheen

name: Furled Finger's Trick-mirror
description: A small, clouded mirror that reflects a flesh-and-blood figure. Makes the bearer take on the appearance of a Host of Fingers One of the ritual implements created by the Tarnished to deceive invaders.

name: Crucible Feather Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from feathers that embody the aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago.

name: Daedicar's Woe
description: Disturbing likeness of a woman whose skin was flayed. She smiles with a serene tenderness.

name: Host's Trick-mirror
description: A small, clouded mirror that reflects a flesh-and-blood figure.

name: Entwining Umbilical Cord
description: Mysterious circular object that's oddly warped. Changes the demeanour of the wearer's actions.

name: Ancient Dragons' Lightning Strike
description: A secret incantation of the capital's ancient dragon cult.

description: A Blood Oath incantation, shared from the Lord of Blood's power. Releases a swarm of bloodflies before the caster to assault foes. The vile swarm deals damage and builds up onset of blood loss. This incantation can be cast while in motion. The new palace of the Lord of Blood lies in a swamp of festering blood, and these flies are said to spawn from excrement in that land.

name: The Flame Of Frenzy
description: Incantation originating from the maddening Three Fingers.

name: Theodorix's Magma
description: Superior incantation of Dragon Communion. Channels the power of the great wyrm Theodorix. Transforms caster into a great wyrm to spew a large volume of magma breath. Allows one follow-up attack. The name of the ancient troll warrior Theodorix lives on — as a hero of the War against the Giants.

name: Unendurable Frenzy
description: Incantation originating from the maddening Three Fingers. Causes the yellow flame of frenzy to violently burst forth from the caster's eyes. Hold to continue channeling the flame. This incantation can be used while in motion. It is the maddening pain and unstoppable tears of those afflicted with the flame of frenzy brought into being.

name: Triple Rings Of Light
description: One of the incantations of the Golden Order fundamentalists. Produces three rings of light and fires them forwards. The rings of light return to a position close to the caster before disappearing. This incantation can be cast repeatedly. A gift from the young Ivliquella to his father, Radagon.

description: Incantation of Vyke, knight of the Roundtable Hold.

name: Urgent Heal
description: Incantation of the Two Fingers faithful.

name: Wrath Of Gold
description: Superior Erdtree Worship incantation. Produces a golden shockwave that knocks back nearby foes. Charging increases the size of the shockwave. This incantation was discovered when the Elden Ring was shattered, and it was feared as a sign of the Erdtree's wrath.
